ic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShaan%20Shaikh%2C%20the%20deputy%20director%20of%20the%20Missle%20Defense%20Project%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20many%20long-range%20ballistic%20missiles%20reach%20hypersonic%20speeds%20in%20their%20terminal%20phase.%20This%20means%20they%20travel%20at%20Mach%205%20%E2%80%94%20five%20times%20the%20speed%20of%20sound%20or%20over%203%2C800%20miles%20per%20hour%20%E2%80%94%20or%20faster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20true%20hypersonic%20capabilities%20are%20based%20on%20more%20than%20just%20speed%20and%20depend%20on%20whether%20the%20missile%20can%20sustain%20that%20extreme%20speed%20and%20maneuver%20effectively%20during%20flight.%20It's%20unclear%20as%20to%20whether%20the%20Fattah%20meets%20all%20of%20the%20criteria%2C%20but%20it%20does%20appear%20to%20be%20able%20to%20maneuver%20in%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFarzin%20Nadimi%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20The%20Washington%20Institute%20for%20Near%20East%20Policy%20and%20an%20expert%20in%20Iranian%20security%20and%20defense%20affairs%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20there%20are%20indications%20that%20Iran%20launched%20a%20large%20number%20of%20Fattahs%20in%20the%20attack%2C%20adding%20that%20photographic%20evidence%20of%20fallen%20debris%20revealed%20characteristics%20consistent%20with%20the%20missile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222174%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Iranian%20missiles%20in%20the%20sky%20above%20Jerusalem%20on%20October%201.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66feea64a7031864927f476b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221444%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIranian%20missiles%20in%20the%20sky%20above%20Jerusalem%20on%20October%201.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20by%20Chen%20Junqing%2FXinhua%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20analysts%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FAmirIGM%2Fstatus%2F1841249755340411305%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epointed%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20online%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Flive%2F2024%2F10%2F01%2Fworld%2Fisrael-lebanon-hezbollah%2Firan-appears-to-have-used-its-most-advanced-missiles-in-the-attack-on-israel%3Fsmid%3Durl-share%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimagery%20of%20missile%20debris%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggests%20the%20wreckage%20could%20have%20been%20from%20the%20Fattah%20or%20Iran's%20Kheibarshekan%2C%20another%20medium-range%20ballistic%20missile%20with%20similar%20characteristics%2C%20including%20its%20booster%20section.%20Experts%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Firanian-missile-strike-israel-shows-capability-greater-scale-complexity-2024-10-02%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20both%20missiles%20were%20used%20in%20the%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENadimi%20and%20Shaikh%20said%20they%20don't%20believe%20Iran%20used%20the%20Fattah%20during%20its%20April%20attack%20on%20Israel%2C%20when%20Tehran%20fired%20more%20than%20300%20missiles%20and%20drones%20at%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConflict%20analysts%20at%20the%20Institute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20War%20said%20Iran's%20Tuesday%20attack%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.understandingwar.org%2Fbackgrounder%2Firan-update-october-2-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eappeared%20to%20have%20been%20more%20effective%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20evading%20Israeli%20air%20defenses%20than%20its%20April%20bombardment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%2C%20Iran%20launched%20a%20much%20larger%20barrage%20overall%20with%20around%20170%20attack%20drones%2C%2030%20cruise%20missiles%2C%20and%20120%20ballistic%20missiles.%20Nearly%20all%20of%20these%20threats%20were%20intercepted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225338%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22People%20sit%20on%20the%20debris%20of%20an%20Iranian%20missile%20intercepted%20by%20Israel%20on%20October%202.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66feeaa63f2165d71