on%20Thursday%20on%20concerns%20a%20wider%20conflict%20could%20disrupt%20crude%20oil%20flows%20from%20the%20region%20-%20for%20example%20if%20Israel%20chose%20to%20target%20Iranian%20oil%20infrastructure%20which%20in%20turn%20could%20trigger%20retaliation%20from%20Iran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20is%20not%20clear%20that%20this%20will%20translate%20into%20the%20kind%20of%20sustained%2C%20sharper%20rises%20that%20motorists%20start%20to%20notice%20at%20the%20fuel%20pump.%20Analysts%20point%20out%20that%20the%20United%20States%20has%20high%20levels%20of%20crude%20oil%20inventories%20while%20OPEC-producing%20nations%20have%20enough%20spare%20capacity%20to%20smooth%20out%20the%20impact%20of%20disruptions%2C%20at%20least%20in%20the%20short%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHOW%20ARE%20ECONOMIC%20POLICYMAKERS%20REACTING%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20always%2C%20central%20bankers%20stress%20that%20their%20job%20is%20to%20look%20beyond%20unpredictable%2C%20one-off%20shocks%20to%20the%20economy%20and%20instead%20focus%20on%20the%20deeper%2C%20underlying%20trends.%20But%20they%20cannot%20afford%20to%20totally%20ignore%20geopolitical%20events%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBank%20of%20England%20Governor%20Andrew%20Bailey%20told%20The%20Guardian%20newspaper%20that%20the%20bank%20could%20move%20more%20aggressively%20to%20cut%20interest%20rates%20if%20inflation%20pressures%20continue%20to%20weaken%20-%20suggesting%20central%20bankers%20for%20now%20did%20not%20see%20the%20Middle%20East%20conflict%20as%20a%20major%20threat%20to%20their%20attempts%20to%20temper%20inflation.%20Bailey%20said%20there%20seemed%20to%20be%20a%20commitment%20to%20keep%20oil%20markets%20stable%20but%20he%20also%20said%20the%20conflict%20could%20yet%20push%20up%20oil%20prices%20if%20things%20keep%20escalating.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESweden's%20Riksbank%20Deputy%20Governor%20Per%20Jansson%20delivered%20a%20similar%20message%2C%20saying%20the%20effects%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%20conflict%20were%20not%20yet%20enough%20to%20warrant%20scratching%20economic%20forecasts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20said%20on%20Thursday%20an%20escalation%20of%20the%20conflict%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20could%20have%20significant%20economic%20ramifications%20for%20the%20region%20and%20the%20global%20economy%2C%20but%20commodity%20prices%20remain%20below%20the%20highs%20of%20the%20past%20year.%20It%20was%20too%20early%20to%20predict%20specific%20impacts%20on%20the%20global%20economy%2C%20IMF%20spokesperson%20Julie%20Kozack%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWHEN%20WILL%20ANY%20IMPACT%20BECOME%20MORE%20EVIDENT%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20context%2C%20Brent%20crude%20futures%20are%20currently%20around%20%2475%20a%20barrel%2C%20well%20below%20their%20%2484%20level%20at%20the%20time%20of%20Hamas'%20Oct.%207%20strike%20on%20Israel%20nearly%20a%20year%20ago%20and%20far%20off%20the%20%24130%20highs%20reached%20after%20Russia's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20in%20February%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEurope%20would%20be%20exposed%20to%20rising%20oil%20prices%20because%2C%20unlike%20the%20United%20States%2C%20it%20has%20no%20major%20domestic%20oil%20production.%20But%20even%20there%2C%20policymakers%20estimate%20a%20durable%2010%25%20rise%20in%20prices%20would%20be%20needed%20to%20push%20up%20inflation%20by%20just%200.1%20percentage%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20economic%20impacts%20of%20an%20all-out%20war%20that%20led%20to%20wider%20attacks%20on%20energy%20infrastructure%20throughout%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20Gulf%20regions%20plus%20further%20disruptions%20to%20trade%20routes%20through%20the%20Red%20Sea%2C%20would%20be%20more%20tangible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOxford%20Economics%20estimated%20such%20a%20scenario%20would%20spike%20oil%20prices%20up%20to%20%24130%20and%20knock%200.4%20percentage%20points%20off%20global%20output%20growth%20next%20year%2C%20which%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20currently%20sees%20at%20arou